cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about mathematical logic and its applications to computer science.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as linear logic has been used to study programming languages and type systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as linear logic has been applied to various areas of AI, such as natural language processing and reasoning.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the decidability properties of linear logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may touch upon graph theory and proof nets, which have connections to data structures and algorithms.
